FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://crimecast.xyz/api

# CrimeCast

CrimeCast is an API that allows users to access crime data for Austin neighborhoods, paired with demographics and analysis
# Group Crimes

## Crimes [/crimes]
### Get a list of all the crimes [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
        
        {
            "crimes" : [
                12345,
                12346,
                12347,
                12348,
                12349
            ]
        }

## Single Crime [/crime?crime_id={crime_id}]

+ Parameters 
    + crime_id (number) - Unique id of the crime requested
    
### Information about a specific crime [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
        
        {
            "id": 12345,
            "address": "123 Street Name Dr",
            "crime_type": 22222,
            "zipcode": 33333,
            "date": "1-1-2016"
            "nearby_crimes" : [
                12346,
                12347,
                12348,
                12349
            ]
        }

# Group Weeks

## Weeks [/weeks]
### Get a list of all the weeks [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
        
        {
            "weeks" : [
                1,
                2,
                3,
                4,
                5
            ]
        }


## Week [/week?week_id={week_id}]

+ Parameters 
    + week_id (number) - Unique id of the week requested

### Get crime information for a certain week [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
        
        {
            "id" : 11111,
            "crimes" : [
                    12345,
                    12346,
                    12347
            ],
            "start_date":"1-1-2015",
            "end_date":"1-7-2015",
            "popular_crime":1,
            demographics: {
                "number_sampled" : 50000
                "breakdown" : {
                    "1-1-2016" : "10%",
                    "1-2-2016" : "20%",
                    "1-3-2016" : "40%",
                    "1-4-2016" : "20%",
                    "1-5-2016" : "10%"
                    "1-6-2016" : "0%"
                    "1-7-2016" : "0%"
                }
            }                
        }

